"milestone":null,"comments":8,"created_at":"2012-12-26t10:03:57z","updated_at":"2013-03-07t17:09:46z","closed_at":"2013-03-07t17:09:46z","pull_request":{"html_url":null,"diff_url":null,"patch_url":null},"body":"* with server version 4.5.5\r\n\r\ni noticed the following problem:\r\n\r\nusing the browser client and clicking onto the delete \"cross\", i wanted to delete my folder \"/photos\" in my owncloud repo.\r\n\r\ni noticed that visiting the directory with my android client and browser client, the directory appeared to be empty (= no files were shown), but the directory could **not be deleted** and still exists.\r\n\r\nusing the windows client i could find the reason:\r\n\r\nthere was this \"thumbs.db\" file, which was most likely be created when i once previewed the /photos directory with the windows clients.\r\n\r\n\r\n### two suggestions for owncloud improvement:\r\n\r\n* add a mode \"show hidden files\"\r\n* when deleting directories in case of existing hidden files: prompt the user \"there are hidden files which prevent the immediate deletion of this directory. do you want to delete the directoy including all hidden files now?\"\r\n\r\n\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"raydiation","id":195053,"avatar_url":"https://gravatar.com/avatar/aa0d7b7302e0d7f4f9513c23b571383a?d=https%3a%2f%2fidenticons.github.com%2faf0a25e27510f77d97634a6bbe653b13.png&r=x","gravatar_id":"aa0d7b7302e0d7f4f9513c23b571383a","url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation","html_url":"https://github.com/raydiation","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiation/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/raydiat